layers.nm: Deodarant - which may or may not be followed by a rushed but heated debate about whether roll-ons are worth the benefit to the environment, when they get all nasty and stick to your body hair - and lots of it, and an equally liberal dose of dry shampoo, and that’s what we used to call back in those days a Glasgow Shower.  Glasgow Showers pulled us out of cosy bed-wombs, sometimes occupied by some drug-bombed, questionably employed boy, sometimes not, and launches us out into a street most likely dappled with the rinse of cigarette-rain, and into the cheap, fake leather hug of a Hampden Cab. The cab would lurch from side-to-side as tricky as a boat, and the driver - Glasgow cabbies being chronic over-sharers - would chatter away like some Monday morning, theme-park ride narrator about their divorce, their nephew with the drug problem, their raving days in the 90s, Brexit, the Missus, and always, invitably who - if anyone! - would be getting their next vote.
